                <p><strong>Attention:</strong> Scambook users, <a href="http://www.scambook.com/blog/2012/03/hang-up-the-phone-scam-alert/">if you potentially receive a phone call from someone claiming to work at Microsoft</a>, HANG UP! Or have you received a call form them claiming they found a virus on your account? If so, it's a scam!</p>
<p><strong>How this scam works:</strong></p>
<p>An alleged "Microsoft" representative  (the scammer) will call you and say they are making courtesy phone calls to all their users alerting them of any "warnings" or "errors" that were found on your computer. We know what you're thinking, "sounds fishy". Always go with your gut instinct, if it sounds weird or too good to be true then it probably is.</p>
<p>Some of our users have already received phone calls and said this, "<a href="http://www.scambook.com/report/view/47178/scamPCcare-False-Advertising-for-0.00-on-12-14-2011">I kept the guy talking on the phone, whilst I checked out the website and phone numbers for known scams</a>."</p>
